{"title_page": "Resham Tipnis", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name       = Resham Tipnis\n| image      = Resham Tipnis (cropped) attending the launch of Sai Deodhar & Shakti Anand \u2018Thoughtrain Entertainment\u2019.jpg\n| caption    = \n| occupation = Actress\n| spouse     = [[Sanjeev Seth]] (1993\u20132004)\n| known_for  = [[Bigg Boss Marathi 1]]\n| birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date|20|1993}}<ref name=\"age\"/>\n}}\n'''Resham Tipnis''' is an Indian television actress. She did a small role of Anjali Sinha in [[Shah Rukh Khan]] starrer film ''[[Baazigar]]'' in 1992. She acted in many serials notably ''Campus Serial'' in 1994. Previously she played the role of Saroj in ''[[Do Dil Ek Jaan]]'' on [[Life OK]]. She played a role as Babita in [[Satrangi Sasural]]. She has also done some Marathi films. She participated in the reality show ''[[Bigg Boss Marathi 1]]'' in 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Marathi actresses celebrate friendship - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/While-we-often-hear-of-cat-fights-among-Bollywood-actresses-Marathi-actresses-are-more-of-a-gang-of-girls-partying-together/articleshow/22483364.cms? |accessdate=24 January 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=12 January 2017 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://lifestyle.in.msn.com/gallery.aspx?cp-documentid=4884186&page=15 |title=Archived copy |access-date=17 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110817155826/http://lifestyle.in.msn.com/gallery.aspx?cp-documentid=4884186&page=15 |archive-date=17 August 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nTipnis married actor [[Sanjeev Seth]] in 1993 at the age of 20, but they divorced in 2004.<ref name=\"age\">{{cite news |title=Resham and Sanjeev |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/bigg-boss-marathi-lesser-known-facts-about-contestant-resham-tipnis-life/photostory/63803168.cms?picid=63803939 |accessdate=24 January 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=17 April 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/I-regret-my-divorce-Resham-Tipnis/articleshow/17532761.cms|title=I regret my divorce: Resham Tipnis - Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Wedding-bells/articleshow/4011714.cms|title=Wedding bells! - Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref> They have two children, Rishika and Manav.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/Resham-moves-on-/articleshow/15710502.cms|title=Resham moves on...|website=Mumbai Mirror|accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref> As of 2018, she is in a relationship with Sandesh Kirtikar.<ref>{{cite news |title=Resham Tipnis writes an adorable message on her son\u2019s birthday - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/resham-tipnis-writes-an-adorable-message-on-her-sons-birthday/articleshow/65952451.cms |accessdate=24 January 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=25 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n* ''[[Zee Horror Show]]''\n* ''[[Campus]]'' as Anjali Narang\n* ''[[Shrimaan Shrimati]]''\n* ''Rani Ketaki Ki Kahani'' as Madan\n* ''[[Saheb Biwi Aur Boss]]'' as Mandodari\n* ''[[Woh Rehne Waali Mehlon Ki]]''\n* ''Mujhse Kuch Kehti Yeh... Khamoshiyan'' as Asavari Bhonsle \n* ''[[Do Dil Ek Jaan]]'' as Saroj\n* ''[[Ghar Ek Sapnaa]]'' as Trisha\n* ''[[Chandan Ka Palna Resham Ki Dori]]'' as Shikha\n* ''[[Basera (2009 TV series)|Basera]]'' as Rasiki\n* ''[[Baa Bahoo Aur Baby]]'' as Devki\n* ''[[Karishma \u2013 The Miracles of Destiny]]'' as Natasha\n* ''[[Satrangi Sasural]]'' as Babita\n* ''[[Tu Tu Main Main]]'' Radha After surgery Guddie\n* ''[[Half Marriage (TV series)|Half Marriage]]''\n* ''[[Bigg Boss Marathi 1]]'' as Contestant\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''[[Satvapariksha]] (2000)- as lavni dancer\n* ''[[Baazigar]]'' (1993) - as Anjali Sinha\n* '''''Bhishma pratingya''''' (oriya movie)-1993- As lead Heroine .\n* [[Khabardaar film in an item song Payal Baje chham chham]]\n* [[Man Sanman]] (2009)- as good woman\n* ''[[Jai Ho (film)|Jai Ho]]'' (2014) - Heroine Daisy Shah's mother\n* ''[[Premasathi Coming Suun]]'' (2014)\n* Be dune Sade chaar (Marathi film) (2014)\n* ''[[Mere Yaar Ki Shaadi Hai]]''\n* \"[[Bucket List (2018 film)|Bucket list]]\" (2018)\n* \"[[Ishq Hai Tumse]] (2002) Anjali Bhabhi\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Indian television actresses]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=1923936|name=Resham Tipnis}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tipnis, Resham}}\n[[Category:1970s births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Bigg Boss contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Resham Tipnis\n| image        = [[File:Resham Tipnis (cropped) attending the launch of Sai Deodhar & Shakti Anand \u2018Thoughtrain Entertainment\u2019.jpg|thumb|Resham Tipnis]]\n| occupation   = Actress\n| spouse       = [[Sanjeev Seth]] (1993\u20132004)\n| known_for    = [[Bigg Boss Marathi 1]]\n| birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date|20|1993}}<ref name=\"age\"/>\n}}\n'''Resham Tipnis''' is an Indian television actress. She did a small role of Anjali Sinha in [[Shah Rukh Khan]] starrer film ''[[Baazigar]]'' in 1992. She acted in many serials notably ''Campus Serial'' in 1994. Previously she played the role of Saroj in ''[[Do Dil Ek Jaan]]'' on [[Life OK]]. She played a role as Babita in [[Satrangi Sasural]]. She has also done some Marathi films. She participated in the reality show ''[[Bigg Boss Marathi 1]]'' in 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Marathi actresses cel